content.p: The University of Nottingham Health Service is situated in the Cripps Health Centre on the main University Campus, University Park. The practice provides health services for students and staff at the University and their families. The fully accessible building also houses: Cripps Health Centre provides a full range of NHS services including: For further information visit The University of Nottingham Health Service website telephone :+44 (0)115 846 8888 *In addition to counselling provided by doctors there is a University Counselling Service , based in the Trent Building. The University also provides a Sports Injury Clinic located in the University Park Sports Centre.
